I came here for a work event on a Friday night. The music was great, the DJ was really spinning some good music (lots of modern and oldies HipHop) The one star, however, is because of the service, but it's not even the service itself, it's the people who work there. I have heard many stories of my friends, all people of color, getting profiled, getting stared at when they enter less-colorful spaces, and so on, but to see it happen on a night when we're all out having a good time was just beyond hurtful. A white waitress felt threatened by our presence and wasted no time to get security on us, when all that happened was a minor misunderstanding. Just the fact that security were called on us that quickly, a group of black and brown folks just minding our business is not okay; no one even bothered to ask us what had happened or to make sure everything was okay. Nope, just call security on us with the threat to kick us out when literally nothing happened. Fatpour, you gave us good music to dance and chill to, great bartenders, and fantastic drinks,  but I sure as hell will not be returning to your racist establishment anytime soon. Get some new employees, or get them some cultural sensitivity training.

Funny that I have always cycled down Division Street, but never noticed Fatpour Tap Works. My visit here was for a Yelp elite event and boy did I anticipate the event after taking a peak at some of the pictures posted on Yelp. Why? Because I'm a fat kid trapped in a skinny man's body! That's why! Hehe.  I had a great time at Fatpour Tap Works, the waitress Tawni was fabulous and very knowledgeable about any item on the menu. Prior to ordering my food, I had an Allagash White, which was a drink that I saw someone else having so I figured that I would give it a try. As for my food, I wanted to get something different from what was featured in the Yelp pictures, so I ordered the Trainwreck Grilled Cheese w/ Crispy Brussel Sprouts, which the Crispy Brussel Sprouts were a recommendation by Tawni. Not bad, but if I were to order again, I would add them with some cheese dip, which would top them off definitely. FYI, if you are not a fan of spicy foods and decide to order the Trainwreck Grilled Cheese, I recommend removing the giardiniera relish unless you want a burnt mouth like I got. Other than that it is tasty, but I wish I would have known about the giardiniera relish taste because I could not enjoy the sandwich to the fullest.  Ehem! Even though I'm not a University of Wisconsin Badgers fan, but I'am a die-hard college football fan, I got the college football environment vibes with Fatpour Tap Works having that Badgers flag plastered at the entrance. Yuck! I'am 217 born & raised, so go University of Illinois Fighting Illini!  I'm quite positive that now since I have visited Fatpour Tap Works, I will take notice of it while cycling down Division Street. As for a future visit, I'am highly interested in visiting on a College football weekend because very few places give off vibes like I have experienced at Fatpour Tap Works. With that being said I hope you all enjoy, and I hope this review assists you in any way.  Thomas G

Future advise:  Don't throw away anyone's beer while they are using the rest-room, if its 50% or 20% left, if they pay 20 bucks for it, they want the last 20% trust me.  They want the last 30%.  Even the last sip is worth 4 bucks.  If there is more than 0% left, or they hand it back to you, don't touch that person's drink.  Was really looking forward to it walking back from the bathroom to put my coat on and leave, and came back to my chair like, what ?  where's my beer?   "oh it looked like you were almost done so..."  She gave me 0.2 oz taster of something totally not as good, which was completely foam, and pretended to apologize, then walked away to cater to wealthier guests.  Understandable, I won't deduct all the stars, she pretended to try, replacing my beer entirely would have been proper service, but that would require admitting mistake to management, as it was a top shelf beer in a bottle.  I'm sure there's a tally on those. In conclusion:  Poor lives matter too, yall.  That 5 bucks should have been deducted from the tip in my opinion, and might have to be, upon on future visits.  sorry, not sorry.  -1  stars.

I'm at Fatpour all the time, since I live about a half mile away. Food is delicious and the service is always exceptional. Weekend evenings/nights can definitely get a little crazy, but during the week it's a chill restaurant and I can always enjoy my food and company when there.  We recently celebrated a birthday and were able to reserve a private room with a large jenga set and a foozeball table. The room had two TVs and lots of tables and chairs. We had music playing and our own server (Angel-- who was beyond wonderful and more). It was a great time! I would definitely recommend reserving a private room if you have a large celebration or gathering.  We also came here for St. Patrick's Day celebration last year in 2017. We had reserved a table and we had an amazing time. Our server was great and the deals were awesome. We will return this year for sure.  As always, Fatpour will continue to be my go-to bar.
